To be honest I haven’t felt very “inspirational” in a while. Last year was super tough for me and I “tucked in” my shell a lot to try to heal myself. And although I had been outwardly “winning” this tucking in I felt like I was slowly pulling away from everyone, and everything..even social media which I’ve been pouring into for 10 years.

And I sensed some of you felt that pulling back and sometimes worried about how that may be perceived or how that may have changed some perceptions about me.

Receiving this text this morning from @jeiflou sent me into a belly cry. To know that even when I am hiding myself there are still people who see me. Who respect me. Who look up to me. 

Thank you so much Jeimy, for this. You have no idea how this touched me today. Congratulations on all of your success. Thank you for sharing this with me, loving on me, and reminding me why I continue to keep trying to show up. 

It’s bigger than me. 🙏🏽

Love you! 🤎

Everyday is not a good day.

This morning I had a 7am work call that kinda blew my spirit. I missed my 8am workout because of how I was feeling after this call. In the past, today would have spiraled into a full blown binge of things that made me feel good in the moment but shitty the next day. Today is not a day I want to eat clean or move my body or meditate but I’m doing those things today anyhow because I know those things are good for me. I know no matter what I’ll never regret those things.

I used to say I was “treating” my sulking self with the bad habits to make me feel better. But let’s be honest, do they really make us feel better or just send us down a path in the opposite direction of our goals? 

Sending some encouragement to anyone having a tough day today. Try not to let the day take you off. Even though you don’t feel like doing “all the things” that are good for you, do it anyhow today. 

I promise your future self will thank you. ♥️

One of the top questions in my DM is “Do I still use the Trim Kit now that I’ve lost the weight?”

My answer “Nope!”👇🏽 

The only supplements I use from my Trim Kit POST weight loss are these metabolism drops BOOST and my protein NOURISH and to understand why you must understand the use and purpose of the Trim Kit in itself. 

I built the Trim Kit system as a starting point for anyone having a hard time jump starting a weight-loss journey. In the beginning of a weight loss journey most people (like me) need something to get them going! 

If you’re looking for a jumpstart to weight-loss this is the kit you need but if not you may find purchasing these items separately best for you! 

Read more for why! 👇🏽

The Control capsules in this kit help control your appetite and ease into healthier eating habits. Most people don’t really need to use Control after the first few months of use when their appetite changes. For instance, I have a very small appetite today because of Control helping to change my habits early on.

The Boost drops are another story. I use my Boost drops daily! 📌 I eat whatever I want nowadays and boost really helps me to metabolize these meals faster. These drops have been key to maintaining my weight-loss. Boost also helps to fight sweet cravings and contains Astragalus which help with mood swings…something at 41 I honestly battle. 🤷🏽‍♀️

The Renew B12 drops were put in the Trim Line to help boost energy and raise B12 levels as many women like me are deficient. Because I’m no longer deficient these drops aren’t a daily product for me today.

Last is Nourish. I can’t go a day without at least 1 Nourish shake or smoothie. Not only does Nourish really help to fill me up it also helps me get my daily protein in because of my lack of appetite today. It’s always best to get your protein in the form of actual food but many of us aren’t able to eat enough food in the day to reach our protein intake needs so Nourish helps. 

I hope this helps to explain the Trim Kit.

Also, thank you for your reviews of these supplements on our site and @vitaminshoppe So happy my supplements are helping so many of you!

I was journaling this morning and wrote “Do the things you say you will do.” This was in relation to me surveying my life and goals and in particular….my morning routine.

I call my morning routine “Feeding myself.” I have this thing I like to say “Feed yourself first, Samia” and what that means for me is doing a list of morning activities for me before I do anything else. Before I take a call, before I jump on social, I committed to myself to “feed myself” first.

But the truth is, there are days I don’t journal, there are days I don’t pray first, there are days I don’t do the things I committed to doing, for me. There are days I don’t feed myself first. And not for good reason. I just don’t. And this morning I was reflecting on those things. 

Today shortly after journaling I read the passage Psalm 119:29 where David asked God to keep him from lying to himself. And I immediately related it to what I had been journaling about earlier. 

Am I lying to myself when I say I will feed myself first, but then turn around and not do so? 

I’m locking in, again, to “feeding” myself consistently this week. Asking God as David did to keep me from lying to myself. 

Are you lying to yourself? Is there anything you said you would do but for whatever reason just not doing by your own free will? I encourage you to join me this week in locking in on whatever that thing is and I pray God helps us all to do these things so we can stop lying to ourselves. 🙏🏽

It’s no secret the past year has been challenging for me. After a divorce, trying to navigate the stress of that situation while running my business and balancing life I hit a few roadblocks. There were dark moments when I found very few people to turn to that could truly understand. 

The idea of @foundnwell came to me earlier this year out of this lack of someone to relate to and/or lean on.  I’ve been toiling over how I will roll it out, how it will look, etc but God told me to just go for it and figure all that out later. So here we are.

I want to create a safe space for founders and entrepreneurs like me and those alike. I plan to invite some good friends in business to sit down with me to talk, laugh, cry and be vulnerable about what it truly looks like being a founder, entrepreneur and the challenges that come with it, and how we can rise above.

I pray you join me on my new journey @foundnwell and that through sharing my journey and those of my friends you too find an outlet to begin to process what it truly looks like to be #foundnwell

I was 21 when Amirah was born. A Junior in college.

I took a full time job when she was just 3 weeks old while going to EMU full time. I was in orientation at AT&T with a 3 week old.

Because we only had 1 car at the time, in order for Amirah’s dad to be at his 7 am job at Ford Motor Company, he would have to drop me off at AT&T at 6 am every morning. 

I used to sit in my work cafeteria from 6am to 10am every morning doing school work then would work from 10am to 7pm. I did this for 2 years. That’s 6am to 7pm in an office, get home around 8pm and I’m up with Amirah on and off throughout the night only to get up at 4 am to do it all over again, everyday.

By 25 I had 3 children and a Bachelors degree. By 28 my Masters.

Preparing for my monthly 3 day cleanse starting this Sunday October 1st. It’s a way I like to reset in the beginning of each month. A few of you said last month you wanted to join me but it was too late so here is your heads up! 

Before you ask, during this fast I drink 5 16oz glasses of fresh pressed juice per day with my regular 64oz water intake throughout the day. I also drink 2 plant based protein shakes daily during the fast. No solid food. No smoothies. Just liquid. 

Whole Foods offers a great discount when you buy 4 you get $8 off so you pay roughly $5 per bottle which is $25 a day in juice. You probably spend more than this at Starbucks so when you think about it, it’s really not that bad. You may even end up saving money on dining out etc. 

I don’t do this for weightloss but it is an added bonus. Short juice cleanses offer a wide range of benefits such as boosting immune system, speeding up metabolism, and improving organ function just to name a few! 

Let me know if you’re joining me below and feel free to check in with me while you’re going through! It’s always helpful to know someone is right alongside you. 🫶🏽

#3dayfast #3dayjuicecleanse #newmonth #reset

Book Reviews ☺️📚 

The first slide are my October Reads! 

First is ‘The Way of The Superior Man’. A couple months ago I challenged a few of my male friends to read this book. This month one of my friends asked me to read it with him and at first I thought it wasn’t for me but ladies…READ THIS BOOK! As an “alpha” woman (which I don’t think I’m alpha by choice and rather by survival) I realize I am actually living a life and act in ways out of this survival mode that has kept me out of alignment with my true desires from men. After reading this book I get it now…I understand where I have been misled by some men in my life and how I have also misled by even entertaining certain relationships. This book is truly a must read. I’m now telling all my friends to read it! 

The second book ‘Embrace Your Almost’ is what I would recommend to anyone facing the challenge of letting go of your plans and surrendering to Gods plans, specifically in business. There are not many books (actually I couldn’t find any other) out there that speak specifically to this topic. This book has been instrumental to me particularly. I highly recommend this to my entrepreneurs. 10/10!

Second slide is my recent book haul for November and December! Excited to dive in!
